### Music Streaming Backend — REST Client examples
### (Use with the VS Code "REST Client" extension or as curl reference.)

@base = http://localhost:4000

### Health check
GET {{base}}/health

### List all songs
GET {{base}}/songs

### Search songs by title / artist / album
GET {{base}}/songs?search=neon

### Get a single song
GET {{base}}/songs/1

### Create a song (valid)
POST {{base}}/songs
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Dude Trailer Blast",
  "artist": "Unknown",
  "album": "Trailer Hits",
  "duration": 180,
  "file_url": "https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/anars/blank-audio/3-minutes-of-silence.mp3",
  "cover_url": "https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/twitter/twemoji/assets/72x72/1f3b6.png"
}

### Create a song (invalid — bad file_url, empty title)
POST {{base}}/songs
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "",
  "file_url": "https://example.com/not-an-audio-file"
}

### Update a song
PUT {{base}}/songs/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Neon Sunset (Remix)"
}

### Delete a song
DELETE {{base}}/songs/3
